I went the Sean Hannity Freedom Concert here in NJ on Sept. 11th.

It was a regular who's who of conservative speakers. Newt Gingrich and Rudy
Guiliani both spoke eloquently. The list of pundits who spoke was a
right-wingers dream. Mark Levin. Bob Grant. Curtis Sliwa. Laura Ingraham.
Elisabeth Hasselback. Oliver North. And, of course Ann Coulter!

Ann was the best, imo. She opened with this line &quot;How much do I love being
the in the presence of this many right-wingers?&quot;. (There were about 15,000
people there) She took an hysterical shot at Hillary. She set it up by
saying Hillary grew up in the era of &quot;equal rights for women&quot;, when women
were being told to write NASA because they too could be astronauts. Then she
said &quot;And I think Hillary would make a great astronaut, couldn't you see her
wearing a diaper and driving cross country to confront one of Bill's women?&quot;
I was rolling.

The concert itself was great. Lee Greenwood opened and had the whole crowd
singing &quot;God Bless The USA&quot;. Then Leann Rimes performed. Incredible is the
only word I can use to describe her voice. Recordings don't do it justice.
After hearing her live for the first time, I put her voice up there with
Streisand and Carpenter. It's that good.

The headliners were Montgomery-Gentry. The were great doing all their hits,
&quot;My Town&quot;, &quot;Hell Yeah&quot; and my favorite &quot;Lucky Man&quot;, an uplifting song if
there ever was one. Listen here -

http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=znAQoOkkvp4&amp;mode;=related&amp;search;=

This was the first time I went to one of these concerts. Sean Hannity has
been doing them for five years. I won't miss another.

The money pays for the college education of fallen and permanently disable
soldiers. It's encouraging to see all the people out there who love America
and want to support the troops and their families. If you get the chance to
go next year, I highly recommend you do.

TC
